        " سَمِعْتُ أَبَا جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ يَقُولُ : \"اَلْجَدُّ يُقَاسِمُ اَلْإِخْوَةَ وَ لَوْ كَانُوا مِائَةَ أَلْفٍ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5642 - Muhammad ibn Al-Walid narrated from Hammad ibn Uthman from Ismaʿil Al-Juʿfi who said: I heard Abu Jafar Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) say:\n\"The grandfather shares the inheritance with the siblings, even if they were one hundred thousand.\""
        ]
      }
